{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2022",
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "Bundler",
    "noEmit": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "isolatedModules": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "lib": ["ES2022", "DOM", "DOM.Iterable"],
    // Phase 06.4 P3 — Lit fixtures use the same strict-subset shape as the
    // solid-ts analog (strict: false + alwaysStrict). Full `strict: true` is
    // a v2 concern — the emitter currently leaves generic r-for loop closure
    // types as `unknown` (TodoList: item: unknown), uses `object` rather than
    // a typed interface for TreeNode's recursive node prop, and does not yet
    // emit per-IR-prop TS type annotations beyond the @property({ type:
    // Number/String/Array/Object/Boolean }) hint. These are P2 emitter-output
    // limitations documented in 06.4-02-SUMMARY.md (the TodoList scoped-slot
    // closure caveat) and tracked as a Phase 7 emitter-types enhancement.
    //
    // What this gate DOES verify:
    //  - Decorator syntax (@customElement / @property / @state / @query /
    //    @queryAssignedElements) parses under experimentalDecorators: true.
    //  - useDefineForClassFields: false works (RESEARCH.md Pitfall 1 — Lit's
    //    reactive property decorators conflict with strict useDefineForClassFields).
    //  - emitDecoratorMetadata: false (D-LIT-05 — Lit doesn't consume metadata).
    //  - The four import sources resolve (lit / lit/decorators.js /
    //    @lit-labs/preact-signals / @rozie/runtime-lit).
    //  - SignalWatcher(LitElement) typechecks as a base class.
    //  - createLitControllableProperty<T>'s generic signature is honored.
    //  - Side-effect cross-rozie imports (`import './Foo.rozie';`) resolve via
    //    the ambient declaration in fixtures/rozie-shim.d.ts.
    "strict": false,
    "alwaysStrict": true,
    "experimentalDecorators": true,
    "emitDecoratorMetadata": false,
    "useDefineForClassFields": false
  },
  "include": ["lit-ts.test.ts"]
}
